title: Rock from the impact that formed the moon may linger in Earth’s mantle
description: When the young Earth and a Mars-sized body collided 4.5 billion years ago, it left behind dense mantle rock that survives to today, a study finds.

title: Faking death lets some female frogs slip the mating grip of a male
description: Suddenly looking dead, grunting like a guy or vigorously rotating can help female frogs survive mating balls in species with aggressively grabby males.

title: On some Australian islands, sea level rise may be helping mangroves thrive
description: Rising seas usually spell trouble for mangroves. But the first survey of the Howick Islands in 50 years finds that mangroves there have expanded a lot.
